@startuml System Integration - End-to-End Flows

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontColor black
skinparam sequenceBoxBorderColor black
skinparam sequenceBoxBackgroundColor #f5f5f5
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #e0e0e0
skinparam sequenceDividerBorderColor black
skinparam sequenceArrowColor black
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor black
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor white
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor black
skinparam shadowing false

title System Integration Architecture

' Flow 1: Book Ingest Workflow
box "Flow 1: Book Upload & Processing"
    participant Client as "Web\nClient"
    participant API as "API\nLayer"
    participant Queue as "MongoDB\nJobQueue"
    participant Worker as "Worker\nJobRunner"
    participant Storage as "File\nStorage"
    participant Realtime as "Realtime\nGateway"
    participant ClientList as "Other\nClients"
end box

Client->>API: POST /api/admin/books/upload\n(multipart: file, metadata)
API->>API: AdminBookController.uploadBook()\nvalidate file + metadata
API->>Storage: save file to /audiobooks/{bookId}/original
Storage-->>API: filePath

API->>Queue: JobModel.create({type: INGEST, payload: {bookId, filePath}})
Queue-->>API: Job {_id, status: QUEUED}

API->>Realtime: emit('job.state.changed', {id, status: QUEUED})
Realtime->>ClientList: broadcast event

API-->>Client: HTTP 202 Accepted\n{jobId, status: QUEUED}

par Processing in Worker
    Worker->>Queue: query {status: QUEUED} limit 10
    Queue-->>Worker: [Job]
    Worker->>Queue: atomic claim {jobId, claimedBy: worker}
    Queue-->>Worker: claimed=true
    
    Worker->>Queue: update {status: RUNNING, startedAt: now}
    Worker->>Realtime: emit('job.state.changed', {id, status: RUNNING})
    Realtime->>ClientList: broadcast RUNNING
    
    Worker->>Storage: read originalFile
    Worker->>Worker: IngestHandler.handle(job)\ndetect format (m4b vs mp3)
    alt Format == mp3
        Worker->>Worker: TranscodeHandler\nConvert MP3 → M4B
        Worker->>Storage: write /audiobooks/{bookId}/book.m4b
    else Format == m4b
        Worker->>Storage: copy to /audiobooks/{bookId}/book.m4b
    end
    
    Worker->>Worker: ExtractCoverHandler\nFFprobe + cover extraction
    Worker->>Storage: write /audiobooks/{bookId}/cover.jpg
    
    Worker->>Worker: MetadataService\nExtract duration, chapters
    Worker->>Queue: Book update\n{duration: 1234, chapters: [...]}
    
    Worker->>Queue: update Job\n{status: DONE, completedAt: now, result: {...}}
    Worker->>Realtime: emit('job.state.changed', {id, status: DONE})
    Realtime->>ClientList: broadcast DONE
    
    Worker->>Realtime: emit('book.added', {bookId, title, author})
    Realtime->>ClientList: broadcast book added\nLibrary refreshes
end

' Flow 2: Progress Sync
box "Flow 2: Cross-Device Progress Sync"
    participant Tab1 as "Tab 1\n(Playing)"
    participant Tab2 as "Tab 2\n(Listener)"
    participant APIPlayer as "API\nPlayer Module"
    participant Progress as "ProgressService\n(DB)"
    participant RealtimeGW as "Realtime\nGateway"
    participant Tab2Realtime as "Tab 2\nRealtimeService"
end box

Tab1->>Tab1: PlayerService.onTimeUpdate()\nemit currentPosition = 300s
Tab1->>Tab1: ProgressService debounce(5s)

Tab1->>APIPlayer: POST /api/books/{bookId}/progress\n{positionSeconds: 300, completed: false}

APIPlayer->>Progress: ProgressModel.findOneAndUpdate()\nsave position for user

APIPlayer->>RealtimeGW: progressService.emit('progress.synced', {userId, bookId, position: 300})

RealtimeGW->>Tab2Realtime: WebSocket message\nevent: 'progress.synced'\ndata: {userId, bookId, position: 300}

Tab2Realtime->>Tab2: RealtimeService.on('progress.synced')\nemit Observable

Tab2->>Tab2: ProgressService subscribes\nreceives position update

Tab2->>Tab2: PlayerService.applyProgressSync()\nValidate: same book? not playing?\nnewerTimestamp?\n✓ All checks pass

Tab2->>Tab2: playerService.seek(300)\napply position\nUI updates: progress bar moves to 300s

APIPlayer-->>Tab1: HTTP 200\n{positionSeconds: 300, updatedAt: timestamp}

' Flow 3: Audio Streaming with Range Requests
box "Flow 3: Audio Streaming & Resume"
    participant TabStream as "Frontend\naudio element"
    participant APIStream as "StreamingService"
    participant FileCache as "File\nSystem"
    participant CDN as "Nginx\n(Reverse Proxy)"
end box

TabStream->>APIStream: GET /api/streaming/books/{bookId}/audio\nHeaders: Authorization: Bearer token

APIStream->>APIStream: StreamingController.getAudio()\nauthenticate + authorize

APIStream->>FileCache: determine file size (2.5GB)
FileCache-->>APIStream: size = 2684354560 bytes

APIStream->>APIStream: build cache headers\nETag: sha256(size+mtime)\nLast-Modified: file mtime

TabStream->>APIStream: Range request\nHeaders: Range: bytes=0-1048575 (1MB chunk)

APIStream->>FileCache: fs.createReadStream(path, {start: 0, end: 1048575})
FileCache-->>APIStream: stream chunk 0-1MB

APIStream->>TabStream: HTTP 206 Partial Content\nHeaders:\n- Content-Range: bytes 0-1048575/2684354560\n- Content-Length: 1048576\n- Accept-Ranges: bytes\n- ETag: sha256hash\n- Cache-Control: private, max-age=86400

TabStream->>TabStream: HTMLAudioElement plays chunk\nRequests next range

par Resume on Resume
    TabStream->>APIStream: GET /api/streaming/books/{bookId}/resume
    APIStream->>APIStream: ResumePositionCalculator\nget last progress (300s)\napply resume-rewind (15s)\nreturn: 285s
    APIStream-->>TabStream: HTTP 200\n{positionSeconds: 285, fromResume: true}
    
    TabStream->>TabStream: PlayerService.loadAudio()\nfetch resume position\nseek to 285s\naudio plays from 285s
end

' Flow 4: Realtime Event Propagation
box "Flow 4: Realtime WebSocket Architecture"
    participant AdminUI as "Admin UI\n(Browser)"
    participant APIGW as "API\nRealtimeGateway"
    participant WS as "WebSocket\nServer"
    participant EventBus as "Node.js\nEventEmitter"
    participant UsersTab as "User 1 Tab\n(Browser)"
    participant UsersTab2 as "User 2 Tab\n(Browser)"
end box

WS->>WS: io.on('connection', socket)
WS->>WS: register socket listener\nfor user subscriptions

APIGW->>EventBus: realtimeEventEmitter.emit('admin.user.banned', {userId, bannedBy, reason})

EventBus->>WS: notify all listeners\nevent: admin.user.banned

WS->>UsersTab: socket.emit('admin.user.banned', {userId, bannedBy})
WS->>UsersTab2: socket.emit('admin.user.banned', {userId, bannedBy})

UsersTab->>UsersTab: RealtimeService.on('admin.user.banned')\nObservable triggers

UsersTab->>UsersTab: AuthService checks user status\nif banned === currentUser: logout + redirect

UsersTab2->>UsersTab2: Same process

' Flow 5: Dashboard Real-time Stats
box "Flow 5: Real-time Admin Dashboard"
    participant DashboardTab as "Admin\nDashboard"
    participant StatsAPI as "StatsController"
    participant WS2 as "WebSocket"
end box

DashboardTab->>StatsAPI: GET /api/admin/dashboard/stats
StatsAPI-->>DashboardTab: HTTP 200\n{activeUsers: 42, booksProcessing: 5, errors: 0}

DashboardTab->>DashboardTab: StatsService.subscribeToStatsUpdates()

DashboardTab->>WS2: WebSocket subscribe\nevent: 'admin.stats.updated'

WS2->>DashboardTab: emit new stats every 10s

DashboardTab->>DashboardTab: Charts update in real-time\nactiveUsers, booksProcessing, systemHealth

' Legend and Notes
note right of Client
    **Complete Ingest Flow:**
    1. Frontend uploads file (HTTP POST)
    2. API validates + saves file
    3. Job created in MongoDB
    4. WebSocket event emitted
    5. Worker fetches & processes
    6. FFmpeg transcodes/extracts
    7. Job completion emitted
    8. Clients refresh library
    
    **Total time:** 2-30min (depends on size)
end note

note right of Tab1
    **Progress Sync Features:**
    - Debounced (5s window)
    - Per-user + per-book tracking
    - Real-time cross-device
    - Validation on receive
    - Auto-resume support
    
    **Sync Guard Conditions:**
    ✓ Same book ID
    ✓ Newer timestamp
    ✓ Not currently playing
    ✓ Position in range [0, duration]
end note

note right of TabStream
    **Streaming Optimizations:**
    - Range requests (206 responses)
    - ETag caching (304 if match)
    - 1-60MB chunks (adaptive)
    - Auth via JWT header + query param
    - 1-day cache max-age
end note

note right of AdminUI
    **Realtime Event Types:**
    - job.state.changed
    - book.added, book.updated, book.deleted
    - progress.synced
    - discussion.created, discussion.deleted
    - admin.user.banned, admin.mod.logged
    - system.error, system.alert
end note

@enduml
